.TH "rza1_pin_set_direction" 9 "rza1_pin_set_direction" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rza1_pin_set_direction \- set I/O direction on a pin in port mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rza1_pin_set_direction
.BI "(struct rza1_port *port "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pin "  ","
.BI "bool input "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
port where pin sits on
.IP "pin" 12
pin offset
.IP "input" 12
input enable/disable flag
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

When running in output port mode keep PBDC enabled to allow reading the
pin value from PPR.
